div.p:
—that the value of the Canal assets be calculated and recognized as part of the
                    total “compensation” package to Panama and should be considered as a negotiating
                    tool for the United States Negotiators;

—that the annual payment to Panama consist of an amount per Panama Canal ton but
                    should not be less than a low, fixed sum for a period of time to be determined
                    on the basis of mutual agreement;
